{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reinforcement learning (RL) trains an agent to make sequential decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving reward or penalty signals. Instead of learning from labeled examples, the agent discovers which actions lead to favorable outcomes through trial and error. RL is central to aligning LLMs with human preferences and to building agents that plan multi-step tasks autonomously."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "What it is" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In reinforcement learning, an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "agent",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " observes the current "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "state",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " of an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "environment",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", selects an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "action",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and receives a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "reward",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " signal indicating how good that action was. The goal is to learn a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "policy",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — a strategy for choosing actions — that maximizes cumulative reward over time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Core components" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the decision-maker that selects actions"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Environment",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the external system that responds to actions and produces new states and rewards"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "State",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — a snapshot of the current situation"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Action",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — a choice the agent can make"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — a scalar feedback signal indicating immediate desirability of an action"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Policy",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the mapping from states to actions that the agent learns"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Why it matters" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RLHF (Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback) is the primary method for aligning LLMs with human preferences after pre-training and supervised fine-tuning. A reward model trained on human comparisons scores candidate responses, and the LLM is optimized via RL to produce outputs that maximize this reward. Without RL, base models would not reliably follow instructions or avoid harmful content."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beyond alignment, RL concepts apply directly to agentic systems that must plan sequences of tool calls, navigate multi-step workflows, and adapt behavior based on outcome feedback."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Benefits" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Handles sequential decisions",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — optimizes long-horizon strategies where each action affects future states"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No labeled dataset required",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — learns from interaction and reward signals rather than explicit input-output pairs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Adaptive behavior",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — can discover strategies that were not anticipated by the system designer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sample inefficiency",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — RL often requires many environment interactions to learn effective policies"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward design difficulty",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — poorly designed reward functions can lead to unintended behavior (reward hacking)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Training instability",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — RL algorithms can be sensitive to hyperparameters and prone to collapse"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Exploration vs. exploitation",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the agent must balance trying new actions with using known good ones"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "How it works" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "The RL loop" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": { "start": 1 },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent observes the current state"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent selects an action based on its current policy"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Environment transitions to a new state and returns a reward"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent updates its policy to favor actions that led to higher rewards"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Repeat until the policy converges or a training budget is exhausted"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Key algorithms" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Q-Learning",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — learns the expected cumulative reward for each state-action pair in tabular form"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Policy gradient methods",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — directly optimize the policy using gradient ascent on expected reward"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PPO (Proximal Policy Optimization)",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — a stable policy gradient method widely used in RLHF for LLM alignment"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Examples" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A simplified multi-armed bandit illustrates the exploration-exploitation trade-off — a core RL concept:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "python" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import numpy as np\n\nn_arms = 3\ntrue_rewards = [0.3, 0.7, 0.5]\nestimated = np.zeros(n_arms)\ncounts = np.zeros(n_arms)\nn_rounds = 1000\nepsilon = 0.1\n\nfor t in range(n_rounds):\n    if np.random.random() < epsilon:\n        arm = np.random.randint(n_arms)\n    else:\n        arm = np.argmax(estimated)\n\n    reward = 1 if np.random.random() < true_rewards[arm] else 0\n    counts[arm] += 1\n    estimated[arm] += (reward - estimated[arm]) / counts[arm]\n\nprint(f\"Estimated rewards: {estimated.round(3)}\")\nprint(f\"Best arm selected: {np.argmax(estimated)}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "RL in LLM alignment (RLHF)" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The RLHF pipeline for LLMs follows three stages:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": { "start": 1 },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Supervised fine-tuning (SFT)",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — train on high-quality prompt-response pairs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward model training",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — train a model to score responses based on human preference comparisons"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RL optimization (PPO)",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — fine-tune the LLM to maximize the reward model score while staying close to the SFT model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward hacking",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the agent finds ways to maximize reward without achieving the intended goal (e.g., an LLM producing verbose but unhelpful responses that score well on length-based rewards)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sparse rewards",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — if reward signals are rare, the agent may never discover useful actions"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring the KL penalty in RLHF",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — without constraining deviation from the SFT model, the LLM can collapse into nonsensical high-reward outputs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Best practices" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Design reward functions carefully and test for reward hacking before deployment"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a strong SFT baseline before applying RL — RL refines behavior, it does not teach new capabilities from scratch"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitor policy drift during RL training and apply KL divergence penalties to prevent collapse"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluate RL-trained models on held-out prompts with human review, not just reward model scores"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Mental model" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reinforcement learning is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "learning to play a game by playing it",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". There is no answer key — the agent tries actions, observes outcomes, and gradually learns which moves lead to winning. The reward signal is the only guide."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RL trains agents through interaction and reward signals, not labeled datasets"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RLHF uses RL (typically PPO) to align LLMs with human preferences after SFT"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward design is critical — poorly specified rewards lead to unintended behavior"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The exploration-exploitation trade-off is a fundamental challenge in all RL systems"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
